         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/1/96 ¶  ¶ Best thanks, dear Miss Henley, for the fruits of Mesembrianthemum edule. ¶ See M to M. Henley, 9 January 1896(in this edition as 96-01-09a). ¶  ¶ You are evidently highly successful with ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.01.15a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Maria Henley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M32a, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/1/96</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Best thanks, dear Miss Henley, for the fruits of Mesembrianthemum edule.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to M. Henley, 9 January 1896<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 96-01-09a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>You are evidently highly successful with the culture of this plant. The soil of your garden must be particularly well adapted to this Mesembrianthemum, or do you adscribe your success to other causes?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me also to ask, whether the fruits, kindly sent by you, are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">kiln dried</hi>
               </seg>. In that case, or if other<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>wise any high temperature had been used in the drying process, the seeds would not germinate, but the fruits would still form an excellent exhibit in the economic Museum. But I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would then beg of you,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to squeze<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>out the pulp of some<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>fruits on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a plate, and dry it in a mild shady place, not in sunheat, as then the seeds would be almost sure to be fit for germinating.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With best wishes to all of you</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">No more [seen] of the Hartshorn Fungus?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Mesembrianthemum edule</p>
         </div>
      </body>
